commit_message:
import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

Change-Id: I461ce32191cc01fc6ada633be60da98c660cdefe
Story: #2002586
Task: #24332

commit_message:
Disable KVM at OVH

OVH infra hosts are causing "KVM: entry failed, hardware error 0x0"
failures where instances fail to start (cirros, etc.).
This patch excludes OVH instances from kvm enablement until the issue is
resolved.
This patch also makes neutron-lbaasv2-dsvm-api non-voting until the nova
compute critical crash issue is resolved.

(cherry picked from commit 798ce95760e3df09c328f01db9a53866a3d07045)

Change-Id: Ic7b64e535b2283564c477ac6344cd4fdeb170d98

commit_message:
undercloud/mysql: remove useless task for upgrade

This task is only useful in Rocky, when upgrading an non containerized
undercloud from Queens to a containerized undercloud on Rocky.
Therefore, the parameter UndercloudUpgrade should not have been
backported in : I2399a72709d240f84e3463c5c3b56942462d1e5c

Closes-Bug: #1787010
Change-Id: I2b5690dfd3662837b28c9801a0f37e785547f813

commit_message:
Soften guard for ceph loop device in ci script so we can move it

As part of [1] we want to drop tripleo.sh --bootstrap-subnodes
from the ci scripts and move to ansible. For zuul v3 jobs we do
that in [2].

For "legacy" and rdo jobs the equivalent change is spread at [3]
and [4]. We can't merge [3] however because it would create the
loop device and so cause the exit being removed in this review
to fail the jobs

Thus we need to soften this guard here and log a warning. Once
this merges first, we can then merge [3] and then [4]

[1] https://trello.com/c/lrSUMaqw/885-translate-tripleosh-bootstrap-subnodes-into-a-series-of-tasks-s17
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/583195/
[3] https://review.rdoproject.org/r/#/c/15000/

commit_message:
Configure cinder's default volume type

Add a resource that creates Cinder's default volume type. The
cinder::type provider executes osc commands, so this is only done once
on the bootstrap node, and at step 4 when the cinder_api service is
running.

Partial-Bug: #1782217
Change-Id: Ia23996abefdd1410fb86f04ed84a314f4364339c

[{'created': '2018-03-22 11:04:26.000000000', 'message': "Fix: Incorrect replication status on clusters

When running a replicated service in a cluster, the replication_status
field in the Cluster DB table doesn't get updated in some cases, making
the cluster look like it's non replicated:

- When starting a new clustered replicated service cluster.
- When enabling replication on an already clustered service.

The reason for that is that the service and cluster creation happens on
the Service's __init__ method, while the replication status isn't known
until later, when the start method in the service calls the manager's
init_host_with_rpc, where the manager updates the service DB entry.

This patch adds an update for the replication field to the cluster table
in that same place, making sure we have the right data.

Closes-Bug: #1758024
Change-Id: I0d2fded62372a2fc5f49538133c5b66694dccc77
"}]
commit_message:
Fix: Incorrect replication status on clusters

When running a replicated service in a cluster, the replication_status
field in the Cluster DB table doesn't get updated in some cases, making
the cluster look like it's non replicated:

- When starting a new clustered replicated service cluster.
- When enabling replication on an already clustered service.

The reason for that is that the service and cluster creation happens on
the Service's __init__ method, while the replication status isn't known
until later, when the start method in the service calls the manager's
init_host_with_rpc, where the manager updates the service DB entry.

This patch adds an update for the replication field to the cluster table
in that same place, making sure we have the right data.

Closes-Bug: #1758024
Change-Id: I0d2fded62372a2fc5f49538133c5b66694dccc77

This is a backward-incompatible change, removing options or causing them to suddenly abort with an error where they were ignored before is not going to work until we do a major version.  Doing proper deprecation notices here would be acceptable.'}, {'account_id': 21129, 'date': '2018-08-01 16:40:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

Dean, thank you for the review!

I understand your concern about backward compatibility, and the need to provide deprecation notices when behaviors change. However, I feel this is somewhat of a special case. The issue goes beyond the fact that the two options are currently ignored.

The problem is the command ends up creating a new volume, but a wrong one that does not match the user's request. This negatively affects storage quotas, and essentially forces the user to delete the volume in order to clean up the mess.

To use an analogy, the user orders a veggie pizza but receives a pepperoni pizza. Not only did they not receive the pizza they requested, the pepperoni pizza they received consumed resources. This is why the current patch aborts with an error. It's meant to avoid creating a "bad" volume that the user will otherwise need to delete.

I'm hoping you will reconsider the approach I've taken with this patch. If you still feel a deprecation period is required then I'll update the patch.'}, {'account_id': 970, 'date': '2018-08-01 20:08:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review+2

Alan, thanks, that is very helpful.  It sounds like in this case that breaking existing scripts might even be a feature...'}, {'account_id': 21129, 'date': '2018-08-10 14:30:08.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 5.'}, {'account_id': 21129, 'date': '2018-08-10 14:31:22.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

commit_message:
Deprecate volume create --project and --user options

Cinder's volume create API does not support overriding the project_id and
user_id, and it silently igores those API inputs. Cinder always uses the
project and user info in the keystone identity associated with the API
request.

If a user specifies the --project or --user option, the volume create is
aborted and a CommandError exception is raised. This prevents a volume
from being created, but without the desired project/user values.

A user wishing to specify alternate values can still do so using identity
overrides (e.g. --os-username, --os-project-id).

Story: 2002583
Task: 22192
Change-Id: Ia9f910ea1b0e61797e8c8c463fa28e7390f15bf9

commit_message:
Use placement microversion 1.26 in update_from_provider_tree

Recent change I1fd85860c96e8690fbcf93c8a2f02178168bfd5a changed the
microversion for updating the inventory only in the
_update_inventory_attempt, missing _set_inventory_for_provider
which is called from update_from_provider_tree.
It causes failures with ironic virt driver.

Closes-Bug: 1787910
Change-Id: Ibdebd02ce6f52ca87559e9d2d5c068f37bf4b6db

[{'created': '2018-08-17 18:25:43.000000000', 'message': '[DNM] Sprint 18 PoC: *TEST* Settings override

*Disclaimer: This is a incomplete work that aims design discussion*

Leverage zuulv3 inheritance to override config by moving vars
from playbooks to the job definitions. This enables 3 main cases:

  1 - override and add extra playbooks
  2a - override featureset (validation) settings
  2b - configure custom tempest tests

Use cases:

1 Ability to override and add additional playbooks
  * playbooks: overrides playbooks in the top level
    job config. e.g. fs010 multinode overrides playbooks.
  * extra_playbooks: define additional playbooks to be run in the top
    level job config. e.g. browbeat fs053 includes browbeat-minimal.yml
    (but sampled in this PoC with a noop.yaml extra playbook)

2a Ability to override a controlled group of *VALIDATION ONLY* fs settings
   * projects may override a given featureset (validation) config in the
     job definition. e.g. tht project overrides tempest settings defined in
     featureset016.yml like tempest_workers. This list of overridable vars
     should be limited and well documented. For now, only validation
     settings can be overriden.
2b Ability to configure custom tempest tests in the job config
   * set tempest whitelist and blacklists in the job config. e.g. projects
     may define subset of tempest tests to run for a given tripleo job
     (Neutron project may want to run neutron tests only).

Note: Only multinode environment_type is covered in this PoC. This means
ovb jobs should also be modified if the design goes any further into this
direction. Same for breaking it down into smaller changes.

commit_message:
[DNM] Sprint 18 PoC: *TEST* Settings override

*Disclaimer: This is a incomplete work that aims design discussion*

Leverage zuulv3 inheritance to override config by moving vars
from playbooks to the job definitions. This enables 3 main cases:

  1 - override and add extra playbooks
  2a - override featureset (validation) settings
  2b - configure custom tempest tests

Use cases:

1 Ability to override and add additional playbooks
  * playbooks: overrides playbooks in the top level
    job config. e.g. fs010 multinode overrides playbooks.
  * extra_playbooks: define additional playbooks to be run in the top
    level job config. e.g. browbeat fs053 includes browbeat-minimal.yml
    (but sampled in this PoC with a noop.yaml extra playbook)

2a Ability to override a controlled group of *VALIDATION ONLY* fs settings
   * projects may override a given featureset (validation) config in the
     job definition. e.g. tht project overrides tempest settings defined in
     featureset016.yml like tempest_workers. This list of overridable vars
     should be limited and well documented. For now, only validation
     settings can be overriden.
2b Ability to configure custom tempest tests in the job config
   * set tempest whitelist and blacklists in the job config. e.g. projects
     may define subset of tempest tests to run for a given tripleo job
     (Neutron project may want to run neutron tests only).

Note: Only multinode environment_type is covered in this PoC. This means
ovb jobs should also be modified if the design goes any further into this
direction. Same for breaking it down into smaller changes.

Change-Id: I8eae058fa9fcbde73cede1a3b34beba56d12c18b

commit_message:
Update openstackclient-check-plugins to honor constraints

Congratulations! You're the first customer of our fine new command pbrx
install-siblings!!!

Srrsly though - the job doesn't currently honor upper-constraints, but
doing that is, it turns out, hard when you're also trying to honor
required-projects. The logic that handles doing that for tox jobs got
extracted into a tool. Use that tool here to install the code from the
required-projects repos - and pass in the constraints file so that
constraints are applied appropriately.

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/589476
Change-Id: Ic29d2c1bb15479bd0852b74b5d08aac7ef90048e

commit_message:
Eliminate client races in legacy operations

Wait for the legacy stack to move to the IN_PROGRESS state before returning
from the API call in the stack update, suspend, resume, check, and restore
operations.

For the stack delete operation, do the same provided that we can acquire
the stack lock immediately, and thus don't need to wait for existing
operations to be cancelled before we can change the state to IN_PROGRESS.
In other cases there is still a race.

Change-Id: Id94d009d69342f311a00ed3859f4ca8ac6b0af09
Story: #1669608
Task: 23175
(cherry picked from commit 2d2da745931bceeb784984a44d747fcaf6264a30)

[{'created': '2018-08-20 14:25:46.000000000', 'message': 'VSA: Concurrent request handling in attachment

Issue: VSA cannot have two server created with
same host name, so when concurrent request tries
to create server only one request succeed and
subsequent request gets response of exception
of already exists.

This fix handle concurrent request and ensure
only one request with same host name request
server creation on VSA.

Change-Id: I41815510f0e6bf865a46d1efd7b73f613ddbe736
Closes-Bug: #1779654
(cherry picked from commit 8a039bb5cd00baac5e97081621e57820586a33d5)
'}]
commit_message:
VSA: Concurrent request handling in attachment

Issue: VSA cannot have two server created with
same host name, so when concurrent request tries
to create server only one request succeed and
subsequent request gets response of exception
of already exists.

This fix handle concurrent request and ensure
only one request with same host name request
server creation on VSA.

Change-Id: I41815510f0e6bf865a46d1efd7b73f613ddbe736
Closes-Bug: #1779654
(cherry picked from commit 8a039bb5cd00baac5e97081621e57820586a33d5)

import zuul job settings from project-config

This is a mechanically generated patch to complete step 1 of moving
the zuul job settings out of project-config and into each project
repository.

Because there will be a separate patch on each branch, the branch
specifiers for branch-specific jobs have been removed.

Because this patch is generated by a script, there may be some
cosmetic changes to the layout of the YAML file(s) as the contents are
normalized.

See the python3-first goal document for details:
https://governance.openstack.org/tc/goals/stein/python3-first.html

commit_message:
Fix logic around heat output exclusions handling

The logic in the validation was incorrect in that it would actually
error (return 1) if args.quiet >= 2, even though the file was excluded.

This commit fixes that bug, as well as improves the message around
excluded files, which should not be a warning, only informative.

Change-Id: I2cd8cd84a7ebb952e3c39f99a460177b9be9c2e1

commit_message:
Force cinder properties to be set on ly on nodes with pcmk on it

When using the BlockStorage role there is one cinder volume per node and
those are not managed by pcmk. So when we force the property for all
nodes that have cinder_volume we will fail because pcmk is not running
on those nodes. Let's not set properties for nodes that are not running
pacemaker.

While we're at it let's remove *_nodes_count which are not used anyway.

Closes-Bug: #1786412

Change-Id: I42e9f3244bad60b5df2dfa940f132f72c606620e
(cherry picked from commit 81d4dfa7e0c5d4fcc1cd9fae19b860184c6e351f)

commit_message:
avoid Inappropriate ioctl for device with pause module

Avoid using ansible pause which can break if stdout
is redirected.

Lucky for us we can scrap the entire task because
waif_for included delay since ansible 2.3.

See https://github.com/ansible/ansible/issues/41717

Related-Bug: #1784668
Change-Id: Id1398d5cf33a8bf247e3cd812d8180e0582a1a74

commit_message:
Set quota for octavia service project

The default quotas are often not sufficient for a side wide
load balancing service. This will adjust them to some more
reasonable values.

The os_quota module of ansible assumes an installed
block storage service so it is not suitable for our
tests which don't install cinder. Therefore we
are using the openstack client straight.

Change-Id: If85cc3862b9316d9bf43e025bfaab8e1b7fd5576

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I6ebbe927d1d57a139eb2b3867caf7a36a87ce701

commit_message:
Merge extended availability zone response into server controller

As nova extensions has been deprecated already and goal is to
merge all scattered code into main controller side.
Currently schema and request/response extended code are there
among all extensions.

This commit merge the extended AZ resposne into server controller.

Partially implements: blueprint api-extensions-merge-stein

Change-Id: Iebed7756c4599fbf03a5cf1130c047ee8f22d21c

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-02 08:22:27.000000000', 'message': 'Remove octavia_requires_pip_packages

In order to reduce the packages required to pip install on to the hosts,
we use service delegation to octavia_service_setup_host so that instead
of installing software on the target host, and putting credentials on
every target host, we isolate the software and credentials to a single
host.

In this patch we finally remove octavia_requires_pip_packages and finalise
all service delegation and testing.

Change-Id: If3f65fdb8a59a3c41cb8c2f0dee6b2e5a71f05c7
'}, {'created': '2018-08-02 08:27:45.000000000', 'message': "Remove octavia_requires_pip_packages

In order to reduce the packages required to pip install on to the hosts,
we use service delegation to octavia_service_setup_host so that instead
of installing software on the target host, and putting credentials on
every target host, we isolate the software and credentials to a single
host.

In this patch we finally remove octavia_requires_pip_packages as it is
no longer required given that all services use delegation to the
octavia_service_setup_host now. We also remove the task which used to
install them.

We also remove the meta dependency on the openstack_openrc role because
the target host does not require openrc/clouds.yaml any more.

We remove the variable 'octavia_ansible_endpoint_type' as it is no longer
used.

We remove tests/test-configure-octavia.yml because the 'shade' package
does not need to be installed again - this is already done by the role
test preparation.

We finally tidy up tests/test-octavia.yml so that it makes use of
clouds.yaml to make the tasks simpler and easier to read, without
credential exposure.

Change-Id: If3f65fdb8a59a3c41cb8c2f0dee6b2e5a71f05c7
"}, {'created': '2018-08-02 10:38:24.000000000', 'message': "Remove octavia_requires_pip_packages

commit_message:
Remove octavia_requires_pip_packages

In order to reduce the packages required to pip install on to the hosts,
we use service delegation to octavia_service_setup_host so that instead
of installing software on the target host, and putting credentials on
every target host, we isolate the software and credentials to a single
host.

In this patch we finally remove octavia_requires_pip_packages as it is
no longer required given that all services use delegation to the
octavia_service_setup_host now. We also remove the task which used to
install them.

We also remove the meta dependency on the openstack_openrc role because
the target host does not require openrc/clouds.yaml any more.

We remove the variable 'octavia_ansible_endpoint_type' as it is no longer
used.

We finally remove the python-pip package from the distro packages, as
with these changes, pip is no longer required on the host - everything
installed by pip is isolated into a venv.

Change-Id: If3f65fdb8a59a3c41cb8c2f0dee6b2e5a71f05c7

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Ie5d8bef92e51f69111c3b2013a2ed08a9f72a6b1

I believe we cannot get rid of TOCI_JOBTYPE env var until we have two workflows and use it in TQ and TQE. Specially for the reproducer bits.

commit_message:
Remove TOCI_JOBTYPE from zuulv3 jobs workflow

Completely remove TOCI_JOBTYPE from upstream zuulv3 native jobs,
that is, jobs that follow playbooks/tripleo-ci/run-v3.yaml.
Note: 'toci_jobtype' is still declared in zuul config and it's in
use by the old run.yaml workflow.

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I11b8de8245b05453c6e246f250ab130fa21758d6

revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-20 10:58:33.000000000', 'message': "Change include for include_tasks when including loop controled scripts.

We obtain a 'controllers' is undefined ansible error when
the tripleo-upgrade is run without any role related tag
(e.g. overcloud_upgrade, overcloud_update, etc...). The
issue seems to appear at the time of including the
controller_post_script.yml tasks, which content is defined
depending on the result of a shell command. As the command
is not executed during the role importing, the include fails.

The new include_tasks keyword seems to handle this issue
without displaying any error. Also the include keyword was
deprecated in Ansible 2.4, so it's time to start moving into
include_tasks/import_tasks.

Change-Id: I9d10e1d9a95e11fd59bf593bb052abf9eb17cf78
Closes-Bug: #1783303
(cherry picked from commit 629309217b13118ca83016cd9553c8a426c8a31d)
"}]
commit_message:
Change include for include_tasks when including loop controled scripts.

We obtain a 'controllers' is undefined ansible error when
the tripleo-upgrade is run without any role related tag
(e.g. overcloud_upgrade, overcloud_update, etc...). The
issue seems to appear at the time of including the
controller_post_script.yml tasks, which content is defined
depending on the result of a shell command. As the command
is not executed during the role importing, the include fails.

The new include_tasks keyword seems to handle this issue
without displaying any error. Also the include keyword was
deprecated in Ansible 2.4, so it's time to start moving into
include_tasks/import_tasks.

Change-Id: I9d10e1d9a95e11fd59bf593bb052abf9eb17cf78
Closes-Bug: #1783303
(cherry picked from commit 629309217b13118ca83016cd9553c8a426c8a31d)

commit_message:
Correct update operations for baremetal

The bare metal service only accepts JSON patch format for updating
resources. However, we try to sent the whole bodies. This change
introduces support for JSON patch into the base Resource.

The Image resource, also using JSON patch, is not updated here,
because it may end up a breaking change.

Conflicts:
	openstack/baremetal/v1/chassis.py
	openstack/baremetal/v1/node.py
	openstack/baremetal/v1/port.py
	openstack/baremetal/v1/port_group.py
	openstack/resource.py

Change-Id: I4c7866a1246f9e1d8025f5bde1e1930b5d1e2122
(cherry picked from commit 14b460946cd352839d590d84f2b7b04f2ad2559d)

commit_message:
Add a house rule about how to signal appointed PTLs

We've been dealing with how to make appointed PTLs official and
documented in a rather ad hoc fashion: something different each
cycle.

This change provides a house rule which puts the responsibility
and the documentation in the combined hands of the appointed PTL
and the TC that appointed them and not election handling (where
it doesn't make sense since no election happened).

Change-Id: Idf78e00c59d10528a2b4950f8baa93c6731973ea

commit_message:
Reorganise OpenStack-Ansible deliverables

It does not make sense anymore for OpenStack-Ansible to
consider all its roles within the same deliverable as
openstack-ansible. OpenStack-Ansible is frequently tagged,
while roles don't need tagging, as they are only consumed
by their SHAs.

All the repositories following the same branch/release strategy
are now grouped into a single deliverable: openstack-ansible-roles.

Repositories not following this strategy (i.e. repositories with only
a 'master' branch or retired repositories) will not be part of the
'openstack-ansible-roles' deliverable.

Change-Id: I4a528a035d44061d8cec530d6181bbaa40065f27

commit_message:
Clear GPT and MBR headers with dd to avoid sgdisk CRC errors

This change adds a dd before the existing sgdisk -Z command to
workaround CRC verification errors.

Change-Id: Ia1ac4e1c0faf14ad4bb11c2a1c796c93ca8cb5e3
Closes-Bug: #1737556
Story: 1737556
Task: 11496

[{'created': '2018-08-06 17:09:49.000000000', 'message': 'Fix multipath disconnect with path failure

Under certain conditions detaching a multipath device may result on
failure when flushing one of the individual paths, but the disconnect
should have succeeded, because there were other paths available to flush
all the data.

OS-Brick is currently following standard recommended disconnect
mechanism for multipath devices:

- Release all device holders
- Flush multipath
- Flush single paths
- Delete single devices

The problem is that this procedure does an innecessary step, flushing
individual single paths, that may result in an error.

Originally it was thought that the individual flushes were necessary to
prevent data loss, but upon further study of the multipath-tools and the
device-mapper code it was discovered that this is not really the case.

After the multipath flushing has been completed we can be sure that the
data has been successfully sent and acknowledge by the device.

Closes-Bug: #1785669

commit_message:
Fix multipath disconnect with path failure

Under certain conditions detaching a multipath device may result on
failure when flushing one of the individual paths, but the disconnect
should have succeeded, because there were other paths available to flush
all the data.

OS-Brick is currently following standard recommended disconnect
mechanism for multipath devices:

- Release all device holders
- Flush multipath
- Flush single paths
- Delete single devices

The problem is that this procedure does an innecessary step, flushing
individual single paths, that may result in an error.

Originally it was thought that the individual flushes were necessary to
prevent data loss, but upon further study of the multipath-tools and the
device-mapper code it was discovered that this is not really the case.

After the multipath flushing has been completed we can be sure that the
data has been successfully sent and acknowledge by the device.

Closes-Bug: #1785669
Change-Id: I10f7fea2d69d5d9011f0d5486863a8d9d8a9696e

commit_message:
Drop non-voting jobs and increase timeout by 20 minutes

We seem to have a lot of jobs that timeout but seem to be very
close to completing, so let's bump the timeout by 20 minutes.

To make up for it, we drop most of our non-voting jobs because
they are taking up resources and always failing.  This should
decrease the amount of resources we're consuming.

Hopefully, we can bring these jobs back.

Change-Id: I276a022b71fee3b62bd60ae6d47bd22ac3152081

With the improved error handling, do_all.sh is finding errors. Rather
than starting from scratch each time it is run, allow the caller to
just remove the team that has failed most recently and run it
again. Teams that exist are skipped, saving time in finding more errors.

commit_message:
make do_all.sh faster

With the improved error handling, do_all.sh is finding errors. Rather
than starting from scratch each time it is run, allow the caller to
just remove the team that has failed most recently and run it
again. Teams that exist are skipped, saving time in finding more errors.

Change-Id: I091765d397afecd5980dae8d389e07119cd2ac8e
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

Use new infra tox-docs templates

Use the newly defined templates everywhere.
Update storyboard jobs, we can use the templates directly. Publishing
happens with each merge for storyboard but only on release for the
client, so update the templates and remove extra job variants.

commit_message:
Add a simple baremetal functional job

This creates a new job with a limites set of services, including
ironic. Since many regular tests won't work with the baremetal
backend or will take too much, only baremetal tests are run in it.

Change-Id: Ia8af5ebc9aec46d405180f6894dd4228eb816b59

commit_message:
Switch infra docs job to new PTI

Create new infra publish templates to use jobs that use "tox -e docs"
directly. These will replace publish-openstack-sphinx-docs-infra etc.

Use new template publish-tox-docs-infra directly for this repo.

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/593488

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Ic0f38b70ad0e2b8491ce3195fa87b6b695551e66

commit_message:
Remove mox in libvirt/test_driver.py (5)

Replace mox with mock or stub_out in the following methods
of the LibvirtConnTestCase
in nova/tests/unit/virt/libvirt/test_driver.py.

* test_get_pci_passthrough_devices
* test_diagnostic_vcpus_exception
* test_diagnostic_blockstats_exception
* test_diagnostic_interfacestats_exception
* test_diagnostic_memorystats_exception
* test_diagnostic_full
* _test_get_instance_capabilities
* test_shared_storage_detection_easy
* test_create_domain_define_xml_fails
* test_create_domain_with_flags_fails
* test_create_domain_enable_hairpin_fails
* test_get_vnc_console
* test_get_vnc_console_unavailable
* test_get_spice_console
* test_get_spice_console_unavailable
* _test_attach_detach_interface_get_config
* test_default_root_device_name

Subsequent patches will replace mox in other test cases.

Change-Id: I530da7aed52d0cbaf0a4451aaf1442c12ed69642
Implements: blueprint mox-removal-stein

commit_message:
Ceph-Client Configmap rename

- Due to recent Ceph chart split, changing configmap name
  from ceph-etc to ceph-client-etc. Also update filename
  to reflect name change

Change-Id: If8b72e8e673aaa9ba1dd112c37a2000aff569089

commit_message:
WIP Test/Fix Multiple Ceph deployment in a k8 cluster

- Able to deploy ceph with different namespace
- Able to deploy multiple ceph cluster within a single
k8 cluster.

- For purpose of testing, we are deploying Ceph with `ucp`
namespace. This will be changed before merge.
- Moved key/values that needs to be different for
each Ceph namespaces to overrides (i.e. labels,
storageclass, storage etc)

Change-Id: I40e8ba4ee791b1add0363f2894e9c6fd84e58a11

commit_message:
WIP Update Ceph install script

- Now that Ceph is split into 3 charts, updating
script to install each chart with chart specific overrides
- This should make it easy to understand which overrides are
used for which chart

subject: Fix KeyError while retrieving value from self._opts
messages: [{'account_id': 25601, 'date': '2018-06-01 22:47:37.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 2472, 'date': '2018-06-02 00:06:21.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nI don't think that behavior really something we want to change. The library is working as designed. We expect the application owner to change internal references to the old option name when the option is renamed. And we do not expect the application to use options that it doesn't own and might be changed out from under it."}, {'account_id': 25601, 'date': '2018-08-20 15:47:09.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-06-01 22:47:37.000000000', 'message': 'Fix KeyError while retrieving value from self._opts

This happens when calling _get_opt_info with deprecated opt name. Retrieve opt
and use opt.dest instead to avoid KeyError.

Change-Id: I55ed8078722483decccf7b9b9ea4a127e7ca78af
Closes-Bug: #1774722
'}]
commit_message:
Fix KeyError while retrieving value from self._opts

This happens when calling _get_opt_info with deprecated opt name. Retrieve opt
and use opt.dest instead to avoid KeyError.

Change-Id: I55ed8078722483decccf7b9b9ea4a127e7ca78af
Closes-Bug: #1774722

variables. Reverting them to work out a better solution.

commit_message:
Use the base Resource's JSON patch support in Image

Note that as a side effect, the image service resources no longer
allow setting unsupported attributes. Their support was a bit
awkward since they were essentially write-only. On the other hand,
this change can be breaking for consumers that rely on it.

Change-Id: I04dc37e0570b84c80d7c19fd090ba7043e70bd74

commit_message:
Correct update operations for baremetal

The bare metal service only accepts JSON patch format for updating
resources. However, we try to sent the whole bodies. This change
introduces support for JSON patch into the base Resource.

The Image resource, also using JSON patch, is not updated here,
because it may end up a breaking change.

Change-Id: I4c7866a1246f9e1d8025f5bde1e1930b5d1e2122

commit_message:
Move nova-metadata api to httpd wsgi

Upstream will deprecate usage of eventlet of all the WSGI-run
services, including nova-api and nova-metadata-api.
See https://review.openstack.org/#/c/549510/ for more details.

With this change we move nova-metadata to run via httpd wsgi
and therefore uses its own config volume.

Depends-On: Ic65736cb0e95c400a728cd699ecf06c6aecff832

Change-Id: Ic46acdbac280ac648ec5ed9d7af0139126334fe0
Closes-Bug: 1781405

commit_message:
MNAIO: When saving VM images RC=2 is not a fail

When executing the save, the return code of 2 indicates
a change was implemented - but I forgot to include that
condition for failed_when. As it stands now the task will
be considered failed which is a bit useless.

Change-Id: Ie8b36335048d2dcf6d0f9e66f8440430f4a68398

commit_message:
A vision

During the rocky PTG, we discussed the vision
for ironic. We learned to use the same words.
We reached the same page.

As a result, the week felt very productive.

And so, we should actually write some of this down.

Accordingly the patch proposes a draft vision, as well
as sets the context of the discussions in an attept to
have a point or document that we can refer back to at
a later point in time.

The contents are based off of the Rocky ironic PTG vision
etherpad[1].

[1]: https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/ironic-rocky-ptg-vision

Change-Id: Ie7208cc5aeade96409b658041b9edb4976512ad7

commit_message:
Change schema hypervisor.cpu_info from string to object in 2.28

in microversion 2.28.

subject: Add FS detection in metricbeat for containers
messages: [{'account_id': 7353, 'date': '2018-08-17 21:25:03.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 7353, 'date': '2018-08-20 14:57:17.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}]
revisions:
[{'created': '2018-08-17 21:25:03.000000000', 'message': 'Add FS detection in metricbeat for containers

When deploying metricbeat there are some container environments that
will have a mount point within the container that may differ from that
of the host; like in the case of an LXC container with an LVM backed
bind mount or an NFS share. This change will now check if the filesystem
within a container has any mounts and compare the return to that of the
provided physical host if the list is >0 the fs checks will be deployed
within the contianer environment.

Change-Id: Iae5827f4e7e0a85eb733128b54d6ef4c8721537a
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
'}]
commit_message:
Add FS detection in metricbeat for containers

When deploying metricbeat there are some container environments that
will have a mount point within the container that may differ from that
of the host; like in the case of an LXC container with an LVM backed
bind mount or an NFS share. This change will now check if the filesystem
within a container has any mounts and compare the return to that of the
provided physical host if the list is >0 the fs checks will be deployed
within the contianer environment.

Change-Id: Iae5827f4e7e0a85eb733128b54d6ef4c8721537a
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Avoid tox_install.sh for constraints support

We do not need tox_install.sh, pip can handle constraints itself
and install the project correctly. Thus update tox.ini and remove
the now obsolete tools/tox_install.sh file.

This follows https://review.openstack.org/#/c/508061 to remove
tools/tox_install.sh.

Change-Id: Ia1ff8e18cd0a9ba82137aa527fc8b6fc1b5e98a5
(cherry picked from commit 6d94ae163dd7822043e3e2097ccde9fdeaa03223)

commit_message:
Resolve stack outputs only on COMPLETE

While the stack is not COMPLETE, we do not need
to resolve the outputs of the stack. Resolving the
outputs is expensive for large stacks.

story: 2002959
task: 22961

Change-Id: I26861214bba8cc92f4e7f9ecba5ba51df99346cb
Signed-off-by: Spyros Trigazis <spyridon.trigazis@cern.ch>
(cherry picked from commit 797f0157d63a9543079a3d91347f7a27293629c6)

commit_message:
RemoteFS: Use summarize option for "du"

Only return the total from du rather than
a full listing.

The parsing code here expects du's output to
only be one line.

commit_message:
[Fullstack] Add debug_iptables=True in security groups tests

In security groups tests with "iptables" or "iptables_hybrid"
driver it will be useful to have debug_iptables_rules enabled
to check what rules are applied by L2 agent in case of test
failures.

Change-Id: Ib7d12b2e589019bc6043affe371ef5aa5425945b
Related-Bug: #1779328

commit_message:
Remove proactive backport stable instructions

This section of the stable branch guide gave an example of a specific
teams process for doing stable backports, using scripts from a repo that
no long exists. This is all useful information, but other teams are
handling this in a different way, and with some dead links to missing
scripts this may just cause more confusion than help.

Change-Id: I6a102a1aa50a917c03f1d81ebd846bdac1770311
Signed-off-by: Sean McGinnis <sean.mcginnis@gmail.com>

commit_message:
Added possibility to specify ssh username and port for ceph mons.

Now SSH port relies on ansible_port variable. On case of using
non-standard SSH ports on all infrastructure, only this role fails on
connection to CEPH monitors.
Added ceph_mon_user variable to defaults. This may be usefull, as ceph
recommends to do all actions with non-root users, so ability to override
user is pretty usefull.

It's not pure cherry-pick, as conflicts were fixed manually.

This involves fix from https://review.openstack.org/#/c/593577/

Change-Id: I01f42287f50dbeb2c6a7f8912e08d21aca2d24b9
Related-Bug: 1773925

commit_message:
Added possibility to specify ssh username and port for ceph mons.

Now SSH port relies on ansible_port variable. On case of using
non-standard SSH ports on all infrastructure, only this role fails on
connection to CEPH monitors.
Added ceph_mon_user variable to defaults. This may be usefull, as ceph
recommends to do all actions with non-root users, so ability to override
user is pretty usefull.


Change-Id: I01f42287f50dbeb2c6a7f8912e08d21aca2d24b9
Related-Bug: 1773925

Previously allowed() methods in DeleteVolume and DeleteVolumeSnapshot
actions assume that the cinder generic group is always available.
The current admin volume and volume snapshot tables do not load
generic group information, so these allowed() methods failed and
as a result these delete actions are not shown.
This commit checks if a volume belongs to a generic group in more
robust way. This change makes the project volume table work with

commit_message:
Make generic group check work with admin table

Previously allowed() methods in DeleteVolume and DeleteVolumeSnapshot
actions assume that the cinder generic group is always available.
The current admin volume and volume snapshot tables do not load
generic group information, so these allowed() methods failed and
as a result these delete actions are not shown.
This commit checks if a volume belongs to a generic group in more
robust way. This change makes the project volume table work with
deployments without the generic group as well.

Change-Id: Idd887434153966d9188acaf08346fa6a0f0e6719
Closes-Bug: #1787065
(cherry picked from commit e5d6f54e99b6252efef578bea92739e939a8e5d2)

commit_message:
Safer handling of return statement inside of OperationLogMiddleware

Enclosing return statement in a try block. If object is unserializable
then return a message.

Change-Id: I184f4b10a419037d3ed770fbec42c262f03a89f2
Closes-bug: #1784438
(cherry picked from commit 27f619cf9b82d720ec83f72e02a4821606394829)

commit_message:
Create publish-tox-docs-infra

Follow other projects and use "tox -e docs" for publishing of manuals
instead of calling sphinx directly. This creates a new job
publish-tox-docs-infra.

commit_message:
fix FloatingIPTestJSON teardown

The following test tearDown:
tearDownClass (tempest.api.network.test_floating_ips.
               FloatingIPTestJSON)

Fails with the following exception:
Details: {u'message': u'Bad router request: Subnet
df1a18a6-972c-45d3-ad37-b4cede3a59ae not connected to router
153c599f-2740-4737-b2de-e651ebd1a5c1', u'type': u'BadRequest',
u'detail': u''}, <traceback object at 0x7f1c2fd97b48>)

this is due to the way a router is deleted[1], the exception
is raised on L3936 in [1]

The details as to why the subnet is not attached to the router
may be a bug in another piece of code or an implementation detail
im not understanding but deleting by port_id solves the tearDown
failure for contrail backend users.

[1]https://github.com/Juniper/contrail-controller/blob/129a3437da3a356b3cabc4c51a4b8498fcff568d/src/config/vnc_openstack/vnc_openstack/neutron_plugin_db.py#L3906

Change-Id: I723598af9da6e6db809fc1b75b29b7b4ffe20656

commit_message:
ceilometer alarm-history should throw error

'ceilometer alarm-histoy' command doesn't throw an
error with an invalid alarm-id.
Implemented the code so that the command throws
an error incase of an invalid id.

Change-Id: I5a5678b6c88d3d41c63be77f6eb44ee7631c9865
Closes-Bug: #1461458

commit_message:
WIP: remove apiclient

apiclient is dead, and the progress of porting cliutils to
oslo.utils is slow, this patch removes cliutils code and replaces
uuiduitls with oslo.utils.uuidutils.

The final goal is clean all the oslo-incubator code.

Change-Id: I5423a2bca654fc990239dee4230bcd59b6d99a41

commit_message:
add fw common namespace

    - this change introduces a set of memory
      related traits for common firmware options.
    - this is an initial set of traits intended
      to model some of the common firmware options
      supported by both bios and uefi systems.
    - future patches will be needed to fill out the
      common set.

Change-Id: I2ba5c81d2bccb191ba130c110c04bcc292e192c5

subject: add firmware (fw) traits namespace
messages:
[{'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2017-10-24 15:15:47.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2017-10-24 16:16:23.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2017-11-10 15:17:45.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2017-11-10 15:21:45.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 7, 'date': '2017-11-10 19:00:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1

(3 comments)

A few of these are not traits, but rather configuration settings, which is not what traits are for. Traits should be capabilities, not toggles for whether some capability is enabled/active or not.

Also, I think perhaps instead of an os_traits.fw namespace, how about having an os_traits.boot namespace, with the following traits:

 BIOS
 UEFI
 SECURE

so that one might reference the full trait string as, for example, os_traits.BOOT_SECURE or os_traits.BOOT_UEFI'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2017-11-10 22:52:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4:

(2 comments)

the reason i chose fw/firmware is that different compensation on a system may have different support for bios/uefi boot.

for example you motherboard may support uefi and bios boot but your gpu may only support bios boot. 

on thing im really not clear about though is can i have a host boot in uefi secure boot mode, then pci passthrough the gpu to a vm that is in bios boot mode or vise versa.

in the ironic everything will be either in bios mode or uefi mode but for nova im not sure it will be that simple.'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2017-11-20 15:16:16.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Workflow-1'}, {'account_id': 11604, 'date': '2018-08-20 12:16:55.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

i have not been working on this for several months os i am abandoning for now.'}]

add firmware (fw) traits namespace

    - adds traits for bios boot, uefi boot
      and secure boot.

commit_message:
Ensure get-pip cannot be modified

We don't ensure the permissions of the fetched file on the
download location. Sadly /tmp is a known place where users can
write files.

This is a problem, as a potential race condition could appear,
where get-pip is modifiable on /tmp/ folder by another user,
leading to privilege escalation.

Change-Id: I041db3412e228efe8a0d9a87f4cfba206482c729
(cherry picked from commit 039d884e29fff2e597fb0660499fd22852c31743)

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I696e3b281bd076c816a4e6299dd791101d6cf139

commit_message:
Ensure get-pip cannot be modified

We don't ensure the permissions of the fetched file on the
download location. Sadly /tmp is a known place where users can
write files.

This is a problem, as a potential race condition could appear,
where get-pip is modifiable on /tmp/ folder by another user,
leading to privilege escalation.

Change-Id: I041db3412e228efe8a0d9a87f4cfba206482c729
(cherry picked from commit 039d884e29fff2e597fb0660499fd22852c31743)

commit_message:
fix tox python3 overrides

We want to default to running all tox environments under python 3, so
set the basepython value in each environment.

We do not want to specify a minor version number, because we do not
want to have to update the file every time we upgrade python.

We do not want to set the override once in testenv, because that
breaks the more specific versions used in default environments like
py35 and py36.

Change-Id: I7bbfe9d9a240a4badf75623e5270afcd24770e5d

commit_message:
Install openstack client, inspector in clouds.yml

Installs the openstack client unconditionally, not just when keystone is
enabled. This allows us to communicate with ironic inspector, and a new
bifrost-inspector entry has been added to clouds.yml in the noauth case
to support this.

Also adds a play to test-bifrost.yaml that exercises the openstack
client by performing a node list and querying inspector rules.

Change-Id: I19dfe3f63ba2c7fea7ce5881d7c8d0dff8f11264

[{'created': '2018-03-14 01:26:42.000000000', 'message': 'Live migration with CPU pinning

When an instance with pinned CPUs is live-migrated, the pinning is not
recalculated on the destination compute host. This can lead to
multiple instances being pinned to the same pCPUs, violating their
dedicated CPU policy and causing unpredictable performance
degradation. This is a long-standing and well-known problem with a fix
in progress since 2015. This spec assumes that the proposed fix has
accumulated too much negative inertia to merge in its current state,
and proposes a new solution.

Change-Id: I1c75c555821e9eb7c51deb7eee17e3977cf45f18
'}, {'created': '2018-03-21 23:50:53.000000000', 'message': "NUMA-aware live migration

When an instance with NUMA characteristics is live-migrated, those
characteristics are not recalculated on the destination compute host.
In the CPU pinning case, using the source host's pin mappings on the
destination can lead to multiple instances being pinned to the same
pCPUs. In the case of hugepage-backed instances, which are
NUMA-localized, an instance needs to have its NUMA topology
recalculated on the destination compute host during a live migration.

Change-Id: I1c75c555821e9eb7c51deb7eee17e3977cf45f18

commit_message:
NUMA-aware live migration

When an instance with NUMA characteristics is live-migrated, those
characteristics are not recalculated on the destination compute host.
In the CPU pinning case, using the source host's pin mappings on the
destination can lead to multiple instances being pinned to the same
pCPUs. In the case of hugepage-backed instances, which are
NUMA-localized, an instance needs to have its NUMA mapping
recalculated on the destination compute host during a live migration.

Change-Id: I1c75c555821e9eb7c51deb7eee17e3977cf45f18

[{'created': '2018-07-25 06:52:56.000000000', 'message': "Run controller_pos_script.yml only if controllers var is defined.

In the playbook controller_post_scripts.yml we
try to register the controller nodes. But if
there are no output from the 'server list'
command we obtain a 'controllers' is undefined
error.

Change-Id: I9d10e1d9a95e11fd59bf593bb052abf9eb17cf78
Closes-Bug: #1783303
"}, {'created': '2018-07-25 10:01:30.000000000', 'message': "Change include for include_tasks when including loop controled scripts.

We obtain a 'controllers' is undefined ansible error when
the tripleo-upgrade is run without any role related tag
(e.g. overcloud_upgrade, overcloud_update, etc...). The
issue seems to appear at the time of including the
controller_post_script.yml tasks, which content is defined
depending on the result of a shell command. As the command
is not executed during the role importing, the include fails.

The new include_tasks keyword seems to handle this issue
without displaying any error. Also the include keyword was
deprecated in Ansible 2.4, so it's time to start moving into
include_tasks/import_tasks.

Change-Id: I9d10e1d9a95e11fd59bf593bb052abf9eb17cf78
Closes-Bug: #1783303
"}, {'created': '2018-07-27 11:06:04.000000000', 'message': "Change include for include_tasks when including loop controled scripts.

Change-Id: I9d10e1d9a95e11fd59bf593bb052abf9eb17cf78

commit_message:
Change include for include_tasks when including loop controled scripts.

We obtain a 'controllers' is undefined ansible error when
the tripleo-upgrade is run without any role related tag
(e.g. overcloud_upgrade, overcloud_update, etc...). The
issue seems to appear at the time of including the
controller_post_script.yml tasks, which content is defined
depending on the result of a shell command. As the command
is not executed during the role importing, the include fails.

The new include_tasks keyword seems to handle this issue
without displaying any error. Also the include keyword was
deprecated in Ansible 2.4, so it's time to start moving into
include_tasks/import_tasks.

Change-Id: I9d10e1d9a95e11fd59bf593bb052abf9eb17cf78
Closes-Bug: #1783303

commit_message:
Adds doc8 check to pep8

This patch adds doc8 check for .rst files to pep8.
Files that fail doc8 check are also fixed.

Ignores D000, D001 of doc8 check. This requires lot of changes
and should be done in a separated patch.

recheck TIMED_OUT'}, {'account_id': 20778, 'date': '2018-08-14 18:35:18.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1

(3 comments)

I tested the code and I can see httpd recycling its file with the few comments attached.
I'm being a bit nervous because I didn't see mysql nor rabbit comment recycled, so I'll continue testing to verify that it doesn't have unwanted side effect on those files."}, {'account_id': 20778, 'date': '2018-08-14 21:33:20.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

OK it could be because I didn't get the entire postrotate strategy, but it seems to me that it doesn't work for regular services under /var/log/containers like e.g. mysql or rabbitmq.

I'd like to start the discussion here..

It seems to me that logrotate's duty is twofold:
 1. it renames the .log file currently opened by a service into a .log.1 (and also cycling the other files into .gz)
 2. it run the postrotate script _only once_ for all files under /var/log/containers* (this is key)

So if I take the case of mysql:
  . logrotate, moves the /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log into /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log.1
  . the postrotate script runs, and deletes file older than 14days, hence it would delete mysqld.log.1
  . postrotate script then sends SIGHUP/USR1 to processes that hold a fd to a deleted file (driven by lsof +L1)
  . mysql service recycles, creates a new empty /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log, and the previous log file cycled by logrotate is gone

I don't get why postrotate should delete currently opened files and SIGHUP the processes hold these file opened.

Instead, it looks to me that postrotate should only:
  . SIGHUP/USR1 processes who have fd opened on _already cycled files_ like mysqld.log.1  
  . never try to delete files, so no log file is ever lost.

I'm explicitly saying "processes who have fd opened on _already cycled files_" because due to config "sharedscript", the postrotate script may be triggered after a file under /var/log/containers/httpd grew too big, and it would SIGHUP mysqld even if /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log is not big enough.
(In the case of mysql, this spurious SIGHUP is nasty because if fills mysql log with spurious debug logs. But we may have the same problem for other services)

So bottom line is: unless I missed a crucial point, it seems that log rotation only works if we stop removing files in postrotate. I have tested this theory with:

  postrotate
    /sbin/lsof -nPs +D /var/log/containers 2>/dev/null |\
    grep -v /var/log/container/httpd | grep -v '\.log$' | \
    awk '/\S+\s+[0-9]+\s.*\/var\/log\/containers\// {print $2}' |\
    sort -u | /bin/xargs -n1 -r -t kill -HUP; \
    /sbin/lsof -nPs +D /var/log/containers/httpd 2>/dev/null |\
    awk '/\S+\s+[0-9]+\s.*\/var\/log\/containers\/httpd/ {print $2}' |\
    sort -u | /bin/xargs -n1 -r -t kill -USR1;
  endscript

Any idea/opinion/disagreement is appreciated at this point :)'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-16 13:49:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-16 13:57:57.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

@Damien, this goes a little bit different for how logrotate shifts the logfiles:

>   . logrotate, moves the /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log into /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log.1
>  . the postrotate script runs, and deletes file older than 14days, hence it would delete mysqld.log.1

nope, it would only ensure the oldest mysqld.log.14 will be purged permanently as there is no more room for mysqld.log.15 (as we set rotate 14). And mysqld.log.1 just becomes mysqld.log.2.

Please do not be confused with the postrotate Final Watcher the find command) duties, which is only to make sure there would be no subtle corner cases allowing some foo.log.X, x<14 to outlast the 14 days deadline. That was a fix for GDPR requirements enforcements. We just do not fully trust logrotate thus adding that find -delete command :)

>  . postrotate script then sends SIGHUP/USR1 to processes that hold a fd to a deleted file (driven by lsof +L1)

correction, not deleted, but unlinked and opened. Unlink happens when a logfile is being renamed from foo.log to foo.log.1 (not deleted).

>  . mysql service recycles, creates a new empty /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log, and the previous log file cycled by logrotate is gone

just shifted to /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log.1 -> /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log.2 -> ../var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log.14 -> then gone.'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-16 14:14:25.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-16 14:15:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

(2 comments)'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-16 14:20:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3:

@Damien , let me also answer to the 2nd part:

> Instead, it looks to me that postrotate should only:
>  . SIGHUP/USR1 processes who have fd opened on _already cycled files_ like mysqld.log.1  
>  . never try to delete files, so no log file is ever lost.

that would break GDPR requirements for some rarely updated logfiles outlasting the allowed retention deadline (14 days defaults), see https://bugs.launchpad.net/tripleo/+bug/1771543 . So the find command ensures the deadline is always met. Even if the logfile gets removed w/o rotations.

> I'm explicitly saying "processes who have fd opened on _already cycled files_" because due to config "sharedscript", the postrotate script may be triggered after a file under /var/log/containers/httpd grew too big, and it would SIGHUP mysqld even if /var/log/containers/mysql/mysqld.log is not big enough.
(In the case of mysql, this spurious SIGHUP is nasty because if fills mysql log with spurious debug logs. But we may have the same problem for other services)

I'm not sure I following. The filter ensures processes got HUP'ed once (not 100% exaclty once), only if the logfile it used to write to got renamed from foo.log to foo.log.1, or expired by the deadline watcher (the find -delete command)'}, {'account_id': 20778, 'date': '2018-08-16 14:55:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1

Ok after a with Bogdan I understand now that:

 . why we only track for file marked as "(deleted)" by lsof. That's only the files which got renamed/"move"d by logrotate. and consequently it's safe to signal the process which still hold fd opened to such renamed file, so they get a change to recreate a log file.
 . the file find rm is just a cleanup of very old files.

Thanks!'}, {'account_id': 20172, 'date': '2018-08-16 15:09:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-20 08:07:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Workflow+1'}, {'account_id': 6926, 'date': '2018-08-20 09:32:29.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: -Workflow'}, {'account_id': 10873, 'date': '2018-08-20 09:33:27.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 3: Code-Review+2 Workflow+1'}]

The change I5029a4b9c76268455812696290aaf82f1a0c2c23 had caused a
regression so that the filter is stopped working and matches nothing.

The postscript command is executed inside of the logrotate-crond
container, like this way:

()[root@5c78303fb8c2 /]# /sbin/lsof -nPs +L1 +D /var/log/containers
2>&1 | awk '/\S+\s+[0-9]+\s.*\/var\/log\/.*\(deleted\)/ {print}'

neutron-s ... /var/log/neutron/server.log.1 (deleted)
httpd .../var/log/httpd/keystone_wsgi_admin_access.log.1 (deleted)

So you can see that the real path should be examined for deleted
(open and unlined) logs is /var/log/ and not /var/log/containers. The
latter is only used to apply the logrotation over the bind-mounted
host path. It cannot affect any host logs outside of
/var/log/containers, so the change
I5029a4b9c76268455812696290aaf82f1a0c2c23 needs to be partially
discarded.

Additionally, send USR1 instead of HUP to reload httpd in containers
gracefully. That part follows-up the reverted
I15fa0eab1625ac63fd57b6a6d5cd22a6ac85f221 as we want to keep that
change and it fits the subject bug scope as well.

commit_message:
Fix postrotate filter and httpd reloading signal

The change I5029a4b9c76268455812696290aaf82f1a0c2c23 had caused a
regression so that the filter is stopped working and matches nothing.

The postscript command is executed inside of the logrotate-crond
container, like this way:

()[root@5c78303fb8c2 /]# /sbin/lsof -nPs +L1 +D /var/log/containers
2>&1 | awk '/\S+\s+[0-9]+\s.*\/var\/log\/.*\(deleted\)/ {print}'

neutron-s ... /var/log/neutron/server.log.1 (deleted)
httpd .../var/log/httpd/keystone_wsgi_admin_access.log.1 (deleted)

So you can see that the real path should be examined for deleted
(open and unlined) logs is /var/log/ and not /var/log/containers. The
latter is only used to apply the logrotation over the bind-mounted
host path. It cannot affect any host logs outside of
/var/log/containers, so the change
I5029a4b9c76268455812696290aaf82f1a0c2c23 needs to be partially
discarded.

Additionally, send USR1 instead of HUP to reload httpd in containers
gracefully. That part follows-up the reverted
I15fa0eab1625ac63fd57b6a6d5cd22a6ac85f221 as we want to keep that
change and it fits the subject bug scope as well.

Change-Id: Ibb017463b0fbbccda035aeb1fff5f6998bbf2d1e
Closes-Bug: #1776533
Related-Bug: #1785659

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: I39bfc3180062b7995687d08bd63b01a335345746

- Added enable_neutron_metering var
- Added neutron metering agent in neutron configuration task

Implements: blueprint support-neutron-metering-agent

commit_message:
[WIP] Implement Slack notification plugin

Right now, Freezer-DR notification engine only supports email.
This patch add support for sending notification to Slack channels.

Change-Id: Ie19f71e9922750fcb295b7c808d423b2c01a1fc5

commit_message:
update pylint

The older version of pylint does not work under python 3, so update to
a newer version. Update astroid at the same time so it is a compatible
version as well.

Disable the import-error lint check since it prevents the job from
passing but the unit test jobs do work.

Co-Authored-By: Nguyen Hai <nguyentrihai93@gmail.com>
Change-Id: I2ddf8985c2b9b6286ddb4cbfd9f3edd2002223c1
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Add sphinx-docs job to Monasca projects

Some Monasca projects lack of proper RST documentation convention.

This commit will help us to speed up the fix process by adding sphinx
jobs on those projects.

Story: 2001687

Change-Id: I5029c8a17bcb3232b2032c61078b371879e80f67

commit_message:
Switch to stestr

According to Openstack summit session [1],
stestr is maintained project to which all Openstack projects should migrate.
Let's switch to stestr as other projects have already moved to it.

This patch also moves "commands" and "setenv"
from [testenv:pyNN] sections to [testenv].

[1] https://etherpad.openstack.org/p/YVR-python-pti

Change-Id: Ic9c99015516c31cbda2a626f8df4ff2f8dc3d852

boostrap-ansible is not run?  IIRC it did this as well'}, {'account_id': 21314, 'date': '2018-08-15 19:19:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

it does, but it doesn't actually download it."}, {'account_id': 14288, 'date': '2018-08-15 19:21:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

in talking to cam, it sounds like bootstrap-ansible is not being run, which the setup-osa stuff expects.  So we should probably just run that before the site.yml or setup-osa stuff is run.'}, {'account_id': 14288, 'date': '2018-08-15 20:27:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

further thinking on it, the bootstrap.sh script curls into python (like curling into bash, smart) and does not save the get-pip.py script.  bootstrap-ansible IS run before the error location but also does not save get-pip.py  (that I could find).

Two avenues to fix that I see.

1. Have bootstrap.sh save the file before running it.
2. remove the `python2 /opt/get-pip.py` line from deploy-osa.yml since it is already done in bootstrap.sh (this means we assume end users run deploy.sh before the rest).'}, {'account_id': 6816, 'date': '2018-08-20 10:03:42.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

This is no longer required due to https://review.openstack.org/592055'}]

commit_message:
Make VhostuserSocketGroup param as mandatory for ComputeOvsDpdkRT role

Without VhostuserSocketGroup configured as hugetlbfs (required by
nova-libvirt and neutron-ovs-dpdk-agent services), guest VMs
could not be created. Add this parameter to the roles data file.

Related-Bug: #1780932

Change-Id: Id8d2b67a116e7458ce398466e2dd2f1e351605b7
(cherry picked from commit db69d36b50edfef35c406c9ea27289b3b555d6a9)

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: If58b145f74443a322bf31fde0820891491588c82

commit_message:
Stop using django-file-md5

Current qinling-dashboard uses django-file-md5
to calculate md5 of uploading file.
But this library has no license terms,
so it is better to stop using this.
This commit remove those parts using above.

Change-Id: Ibe79df0d9d2d583e773cef502e40d07fc3eaf6f8
Story: 2003456
Task:24716

commit_message:
Fix compatiblity with old Pod annotation format

We've changed Pod annotation format in Rocky. To support upgrading
Kuryr we need to keep compatiblity with that format. This commit
implements that.

We should also think about creating a tool that will convert all the
annotations in a setup.

Change-Id: I88e1b318d58d0d90138e347503928da41518a888
Closes-Bug: 1782366

commit_message:
Configure notifications to be unversioned

Beginning in the Pike release, Nova started sending both versioned
and unversioned notifications. The verioned notification queues do
not have any consumers so this causes some queues to fill up until
either the messages expire or they are flushed. This changes the
nova configuration to only send unversioned (legacy) notifications.

Change-Id: Idca18960542b7d7710b8f6c4ee1c579603b0e08b
Related-bug: #1665449
(cherry picked from commit 35a78a049675b590a72cae47315c92a889627cfb)

commit_message:
Set tuned profile for compute roles

Computes should have virtual-host tuned profile set per default in
roles definition. HCI compute as recommended before keep
throughput-performance.

Fixes bug 1667524

commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: Ibc27b828ebd332fbf79edae93657fffd458214c6

commit_message:
Explicitly specify endpoint type during Monasca registration

Monasca defaults to using the public endpoint to register
Monasca endpoints which is bad practice and doesn't work on
some deployments. This change uses the admin interface by
default.

Change-Id: Ia9c5e041e71867fe72aad43e1344cd2107652d7d
Co-Authored-By: Mark Goddard <mark@stackhpc.com>
Closes-Bug: #1787610

commit_message:
Fix lost connection when create security group log

Packet sent to table 91 are considered accepted by the egress pipeline
and NORMAL action is used by default in this table. However, if we
create a security group logging resource, then ovs flows log will be
added into this table with higher priority. Therefore packet matches
with ovs flows log will be sent to CONTROLLER and never forward.
So this patch append action=NORMAL into ovs flows log to forward
the packet and send it to CONTROLLER for logging.

Closes-Bug: #1787106
Change-Id: I6e95e2e646ec8a5507c7f140ab2c4a56be8404c3

commit_message:
Update osprofiler to 2.3.0

Skip the jaeger tracing tests for now, as neither RDO nor SUSE has a
python jaeger-client package available.

This also requires a patch for python-neutronclient which had been using
a private method that has been removed in this version of osprofiler.
This commit only patches the SUSE version of python-neutronclient to
work around a CI issue, a subsequent patch will ensure the patch applies
to all versions of the package.

Change-Id: I300ded49191723c25c82ad59a53ae7e72128695d

commit_message:
Drop nose dependencies

Horizon test setting no longer depends on nose and related stuffs.
This commit cleans up nose related dependencies.

The change was made in horizon Rocky-3,
so horizon 14.0.0.0b3 is required at least.

Change-Id: I25cb4aa6558c599d3c1e334c5281dcb6ca7e3b9f

commit_message:
Update delete group snapshot API exception handling

When a role doesn't have access to delete group snapshot API, the
response code and exception that is returned is 400 BadRequest. This
is incorrect as a 403 PolicyNotAuthorized should be thrown when a
role doesn't have access to an API.

The HTTPBadRequest exception is raised here [0] regardless of what
the real exception is.

[0] https://github.com/openstack/cinder/blob/master/cinder/api/v3/group_snapshots.py#L93

Change-Id: I4a24cd35bbbba42ec3e360ce65fe278edc20d4bb
Closes-Bug: #1783640

commit_message:
Re-use old fernet and credential keys in containerized undercloud

When doing undercloud upgrade, we need to use the old fernet
and ec2 credential keys and not generate them again.

Change-Id: Ib9ef9488a39d5e8f8f99df778a0600dd888ef1d3
Closes-Bug: #1787131

commit_message:
Add user messages for extend volume operation

Add user messages for these cases below when performing
extend volume operation.
1. When no valid host is found.
2. When nova failed to perform extend volume event.
3. When backend failed to extend block device.

Change-Id: I7d2061ac13b2c74745da56feecfe6ed53b284fc4
Closes-Bug: #1773833

commit_message:
Drop nose dependencies

Horizon test setting no longer depends on nose and related stuffs.
This commit cleans up nose related dependencies.

The change was made in horizon Rocky-3,
so horizon 14.0.0.0b3 is required at least.

after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration

requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

"}]
commit_message:
Update UPPER_CONSTRAINTS_FILE for stable/rocky

The new stable upper-constraints file is only available
after the openstack/requirements repository is branched.
This will happen around the RC1 timeframe.

Recheck and merge this change once the requirements
repository has been branched.

The CI system will work with this patch before the requirements
repository is branched because zuul configues the job to run
with a local copy of the file and defaults to the master branch.
However, accepting the patch will break the test configuration
on developers' local systems, so please wait until after the
requirements repository is branched to merge the patch.

Change-Id: If9254fda745d816fa85a4f9e747fe7f03230eb26

We can't just drop the old config option without deprecation. I think it would make sense to add a common option that applies to thick or thin, but the thin one will need to be kept around for a release for backwards compatibility.

Oslo.config does have a way to "redirect" the setting, so if a config file has the old setting it will get picked up for the new config option:

https://docs.openstack.org/oslo.config/ocata/cfg.html#option-deprecation

This does cause some concerns for backport though. I assume we want to get this fix backported. Normally we do not allow config option changes to be backported unless they keep backwards compatibility. We definitely can't backport deprecations too.

So I think what we can do for now is keep the old config opt and add the new one. Later, check both settings where this is enforced. We can then backport that patch to address the security concerns in older releases.

Then have a follow up patch that uses the deprecation mechanism from oslo.config to get rid of the thick option as a deprecated name for the new option and clean up the handling to just check the new name. That will flag the old option as deprecated while still keeping it functional for existing config files. Then the next release we can remove the deprecation info for the thick option.

It's a bit of a dance, but it would allow us to keep to stable backport policy and be able to backport this fix while still getting things set to be deprecated and cleaned up.'}, {'account_id': 21884, 'date': '2018-08-15 12:38:18.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Fix test failures caused by django test runner

Recently horizon test configuration was changed to use
the Django default test runner because nose is in maintenance mode
for the past several years [1]. Django testcase and oslotest are
incompatible, so congress_dashboard testcase now fails.

test_fake.py actually tests nothing, so there is no reason
to keep it. It sounds reasonable to drop this file.

[1] horizon commit 1f80d94459856a8c477310cc0fe4b0e165d8c0c1

Change-Id: I0b99e709fda9c933ec229bb1dde161cf5bea319b

commit_message:
Remove -u root as mysql is executed with root user

As openstack installation guides suggest to run mysql with root shell
user, mysql will not ask for password, so the "-u root -p" is useless.

Change-Id: I5ffa77971ecbcc9210b185a39842140b3acd8147
Related-Bug: #1785025

Thanks for looking into this. Unfortunately, this change won't help. The error in the bug report is:

  TypeError: object of type 'NoneType' has no len()

That means we're trying to load the template with the id None. Since there is no template with an id of None, obviously it always fails (though this would provide a nicer stack trace). There is no case where you know the template ID but need to ask the database multiple times until it finds it - that's not how databases work.

I happen to know all this only because I independently ran across the same bug a few weeks ago. The fix for the actual root cause is Iedba67c5de39dc2d58938da5505dda5dd147c130, and it also prevents us from calling Template.load() with None as the ID (so the code path this is adding will never be hit). I commented on the bug report that it's the same issue as story 2003062."}, {'account_id': 27621, 'date': '2018-08-20 03:09:16.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned'}]

commit_message:
Retry get raw template while loading stack

We were trying to launch a stack where volumes
are created from images, then they are supposed
to be attached to instances. After the stack
failed, we tried to delete it, but it's stuck
with status "Delete_In_Progress". All resources
have been deleted successfully according to the
resource list. The problem was that it fails to
load the raw template sometimes. Thus retrying
again to load else it will raise exception.

Change-Id: Id597a4f65822dbe7aab3947bead7c443ebe57800
Story: #1765676

Use sphinx-build everywhere

Using 'python setup.py build_sphinx' is deprecated, use sphinx-build
everywhere in tox.ini.

commit_message:
Update to fedora-27 for testing

We (openstack-infra) are in the process of removing fedora-26 from our
testing infrastructure. Update testing to use fedora-27 nodes.

Change-Id: I619879553a920fb4e86068711b0e4ec0d2bf1bcb
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

commit_message:
Do not display "latest" badge if repo is not versioned

We do now display the badge for version even on repos that do not have
branches like https://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual . The reason is
that the test is against series - and we *always* set series, by default
to 'latest'.

Add a new option to disable showing of the badge called display_badge
and use it. Repos can set this as part of html options.

Disable showing the badge for api-ref test document.

Change-Id: I985b49412aa1848b915b8f0a2ff9e95867e420ca

commit_message:
Revert "Fix containerized logrotate configuration"

Copytruncate cannot fix the postrotate filter for lsof searching for
deleted (unlinked and open) files. Copytruncate instead makes the
filter matching nothing as it makes files never deleted after rotation
happens.

This reverts commit 67a7dc70f2885b7db2a42bc28c25ece0bbeba3e4.

Change-Id: I8a73819b4aa45813cbac310452b348681496032a

commit_message:
Remove -u root as mysql is executed with root user

As openstack installation guides suggest to run mysql with root shell
user, mysql will not ask for password, so in
controller-install-*.rst "-u root -p" is useless.

Change-Id: I511f39d734702ab3d1a209f7d868f52fb184f1fc
Related-Bug: #1785025

commit_message:
VMAX Queens driver - incorrect condition for an empty list.

The current check for an empty list is not correct.  This was fixed in
the multi-attach feature https://review.openstack.org/#/c/556780 which
is why we cannot do a backport from Rocky to Queens.

Change-Id: I9a87bc1fb64f5c4245777558aae35d1544354d60
Closes-Bug: #1787219

commit_message:
Remove -u root as mysql is executed with root user

As openstack installation guides suggest to run mysql with root shell
user, mysql will not ask for password, so in
controller-install-*.rst "-u root -p" is useless.

Change-Id: I69d091dacf1257bd46040336fc1a97ebd67172e3
Related-Bug: #1785025

commit_message:
Disable KVM at OVH

OVH infra hosts are causing "KVM: entry failed, hardware error 0x0"
failures where instances fail to start (cirros, etc.).
This patch excludes OVH instances from kvm enablement until the issue is
resolved.

Depends-On: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/593452

subject: Disable kvm on OVH infra instances
